<subSubSection pageId="499" pageNumber="500" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="499" pageNumber="500">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="499" pageNumber="500">
As far as known, this species ranges along the Coastal Plain from the coast of South Carolina to central Florida, west to east-central Texas, north along the Mississippi Valley to southern Indiana (Will 1999: 271). The records from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Iowa”">&quot;Iowa&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Jaques and Redlinger 1946: 297), 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Illinois”">&quot;Illinois&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Wolcott 1900: 469), &quot;New York&quot; (Wickham 1895a: 187; Casey 1913: 144), New Jersey (Smith 1910: 205), and southeastern Pennsylvania (Rathvon 1869: 526, as 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="499" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complanata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="499" pageNumber="500">Pterostichus complanata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) need confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
